@capcutapp_jp

@AIWarper This is really well done. The part that stuck with me was that you let Claude handle the camera placement too, not just build the scene.

I've been working toward the same Seedance result from the opposite direction. I block the camera move and the actors myself in the browser (no Blender), then use that as the motion reference. Before and after below.

The thing I keep running into is framing. The motion reference holds the camera path, but it still drifts on me. It pushes in, and the walking tempo speeds up. Do you also lock a composition or first frame reference along with the motion video, or does the camera distance hold from the Blender reference on its own? Would love to know what you pay attention to.

@wtry1102 Blenderを「カメラ設計ツール」として使う発想、これは刺さりました。

自分もSeedance系で構図がブレる問題にずっと悩んでて、参照動画を挟む層を作るというアプローチは全然考えてなかったです。プロンプトで「寄りから引きへ」って書いても解釈がバラけるので、動作の骨格を別ツールで固めてから渡す設計、かなり理にかなってますね。

MV用途だと被写体の動線管理もBlenderで仮置きできそうで、そこまで応用できるか気になります。

@reidhannaford That doesn't look like blender.

